<div id="review_3211388429" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3211388429" />
    <a title="Kevin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8640270-kevin"><img alt="Kevin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1333790654p2/8640270.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3211388429?book_show_action=true">Mar 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kevin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kevin" href="/user/show/8640270-kevin">Kevin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3211388429" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17184435059755299654">A superb supernatural tale of vengeance and what it breeds in the hearts of those who seek it, The Tribe is more than just a horror novel. It is a human novel. It is all of our stories, our hates, our fears, our morals, pulled from the dark banks of our hearts and molded like the very clay into a golem that thunders ponderously on, a monster that can and does live in each of us.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


