  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3978299271" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3978299271" />
    <a title="James" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17330988-james"><img alt="James" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1372694212p2/17330988.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3978299271?book_show_action=true">May 03, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James" href="/user/show/17330988-james">James</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/45141870-the-tribe">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17330988-james?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17330988-james?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17330988-james?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17330988-james?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3978299271" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5267492432162974079">A group of concentration camp survivors resurrect an ancient monster to fight on against anti-Semitism in modern New York but it gets increasingly out of hand as innocent people are caught up in the carnage. The war is over but its scars and trauma live long in the minds and on the bodies of its victims. <br/><br/>With a synopsis such as this, I really wanted to like this book but it didn’t have any real sense of horror. It was much more a character study on the extent vengeance is useful or rewarding, bu</span>
  <span id="freeText5267492432162974079" style="display:none">A group of concentration camp survivors resurrect an ancient monster to fight on against anti-Semitism in modern New York but it gets increasingly out of hand as innocent people are caught up in the carnage. The war is over but its scars and trauma live long in the minds and on the bodies of its victims. <br /><br />With a synopsis such as this, I really wanted to like this book but it didn’t have any real sense of horror. It was much more a character study on the extent vengeance is useful or rewarding, but the horror and suspense don’t really come until the very end; by then, I was already tired of the whole thing. Horror, perhaps the most out of any genre, is so closely linked to the reader’s imagination and the appeal of the story. Unfortunately The Tribe couldn’t get its story moving quick enough. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5267492432162974079" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


