<div id="review_3493328496" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3493328496" />
    <a title="M.M." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13270673-m-m"><img alt="M.M." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1425589930p2/13270673.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3493328496?book_show_action=true">Aug 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="M.M." class="user" itemprop="url" name="M.M." href="/user/show/13270673-m-m">M.M.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3493328496" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16853353744106450830">Wow! This was awesome! Fully 80% of the book was just an interesting family drama about belonging and race and ritual and trauma with wonderfully realized characters. Long stretches without any &quot;horror&quot; in it but when it hits it resonates because it&apos;s happening to or because of characters you understand and appreciate. Not many outright villains in this book (excepting the nazis ofc) but a lot of complicated, maybe even sympathetic, people with their own self justified reasons for doing what the</span>
  <span id="freeText16853353744106450830" style="display:none">Wow! This was awesome! Fully 80% of the book was just an interesting family drama about belonging and race and ritual and trauma with wonderfully realized characters. Long stretches without any "horror" in it but when it hits it resonates because it's happening to or because of characters you understand and appreciate. Not many outright villains in this book (excepting the nazis ofc) but a lot of complicated, maybe even sympathetic, people with their own self justified reasons for doing what they do. And what they do is fucking gnarly.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16853353744106450830" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


